==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cusk
<hw>Cusk</hw> <pr>(k⟦ucr⟧sk)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A large, edible, marine fish (<spn>Brosmius brosme</spn>), allied
to the cod, common on the northern coasts of Europe and America; --
called also <altname>tusk</altname> and
<altname>torsk</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cuskin</ent>⟦br⟧
